<div id="ncwm-woocommerce-migration">
    <div class="ncwm-subs-field">
        <h4>Please follow the steps below to perform the migration. If you have any difficulties while performing these steps, or experience any issues with the migration, kindly <a target="_blank" href="https://next-cart.com/support-center/">send us a ticket</a> to get our prompt support. It's completely free.</h4>
        <ol>
            <li><b>Step 1</b>: Go to the <b>Next-Cart Migration</b> page. In the Source Cart Setup form, select the Source Cart Type according to the eCommerce platform of your Source Store. Then, follow the instructions on the form to set up the connection to your Source Store. Once you complete the connection, click Next Step.</li>
            <li><b>Step 2</b>: In the Configuration form, select the entities you want to migrate. You can customize the migration with Additional Options and Advanced Attributes Mapping. Once you complete the configuration, click Next Step to start the data migration process.</li>
            <li><b>Step 3</b>: Keep your web browser open while the migration process is ongoing. The waiting time can prolong from a few minutes to hours depending on your Source Store's connection. You will receive a <b>Congratulations</b> message when the migration process is complete.</li>
        </ol>
        <p><b>***Note:</b> Please make sure that both your Source Store and your Target Store (WooCommerce) are accessible from the Internet when using this plugin. It will not work with localhost websites.</p>
    </div>
</div>